🔁 Circular Linked List (CLL)
A Circular Linked List is a linked list where the last node points back to the first node instead of pointing to null.
So traversal can loop forever unless you stop it manually.

📌 Types
1.Circular Singly Linked List
last.next → head

2.Circular Doubly Linked List
last.next → head and head.prev → last

✨ Key Characteristics
->No null at the end.
->Can start traversal from any node.
->Useful when data needs to be accessed in a loop (round-robin style).
->Efficient for operations at both ends if tail is maintained.

🧠 Real-Time Use Cases
->CPU scheduling (Round Robin)
->Multiplayer games (turn rotation)
->Music playlist (repeat mode)
->Queue implementations